{"questionId":"21148","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Two players are playing table tennis. Player A hits the ball at a height of 0.24 m above the&nbsp;edge of the table, measured from the top of the table to the bottom of the ball. The initial&nbsp;speed of the ball is 12.0 m s<sup>−1</sup> horizontally. Assume that air resistance is negligible.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/ccab347a90309d9c41de766b489f63b7b8683a43.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The ball bounces and then reaches a peak height of 0.18 m above the table with a&nbsp;horizontal speed of 10.5 m s<sup>−1</sup>. The mass of the ball is 2.7 g.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Determine the kinetic energy of the ball immediately after the bounce.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><em><strong>ALTERNATIVE 1&nbsp;</strong></em></p>\n<p>KE = <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math><em>mv</em><sup>2</sup> + <em>mgh</em> = <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>0.0027 ×10.5<sup>2</sup>&nbsp;+ 0.0027 × 9.8 × 0.18 <strong>✓</strong></p>\n<p>0.15 «J» <strong>✓</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>ALTERNATIVE 2</strong></em></p>\n<p>Use of <em>v</em><sub>x</sub> = 10.5 <em><strong>AND</strong></em>&nbsp;<em>v</em><sub>y </sub><em>= </em>1.88 to get&nbsp;<em>v</em> = «<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><mn>10</mn><mo>.</mo><msup><mn>5</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>+</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><msup><mn>88</mn><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></math>» = 10.67 «m s<sup>−1</sup>»&nbsp;<strong>✓</strong></p>\n<p>KE =&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp;× 0.0027 × 10.67<sup>2</sup> = 0.15 «J»&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>✓</strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"21148","referenceCode":"21M.2.SL.TZ1.1d.i","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Determine the kinetic energy of the ball immediately after the bounce.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"d.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 2: Mechanics","2.3 – Work, energy, and power","Core","Topic 2: Mechanics"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}